The pectinase activity was determined by hypoiodite sodium method according to Eq. (1). In this formula, B was Na2S2O3 consumption of control sample; A was Na2S2O3 consumption of control sample; N was equivalent concentration of Na2S2O3; 0.51 was a constant meaning that 1 mg equivalent Na2S2O3 equal to 0.51 mg equivalent free galacturonic acid; S was the total reaction liquid volume for keeping warm; E was used enzyme volume; t was the holding time; M was absorbing reaction quantity. The amount of enzyme produced by enzymatic reaction of 1 μg equivalent of galacturonic acid per minute was 1 enzyme activity unit (U).1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
